MissionBriefing=South of Honshu, 15th of March 1944||On 12th March a large convoy carrying elements of the 43rd Division left Tokyo bay heading for Saipan, Mariana Islands. Shortly after convoy left the Tokyo harbor a strong escort group, under the flagship of an unidentified light cruiser, joined the convoy. |Three days laters on the west coast of Aoga Island the convoy was intercepted. ||OBJECTIVE:|Inflict heavy losses on the convoy heading for Saipan.
MissionTitle=Tokyo-Saipan Convoy
